[![PyPI version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/synaptik-core-beta.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/synaptik-core-beta/)
[![License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/synaptik-core-beta.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/Apache-2.0)

**Synaptik Core** is the memory, ethics, and audit substrate for trustworthy AI agents.  
This package provides Python bindings for the Rust core engine.


##  Installation

```bash
pip install synaptik-core-beta
````

Requires Python **3.8+**.


## âš¡ Quick Start

```python
import synaptik_core

# Example: initialize memory / audit
engine = synaptik_core.Engine()

# Commit a simple memory fragment
engine.commit("chat", {"user": "alice", "message": "hello"})

# Retrieve it back
print(engine.recall("chat"))
```

*(Example API â€” adjust if your bindings differ.)*

##  Features

*  **Contract-based safeguards** â€” run WASM contracts to enforce rules
*  **Persistent memory** â€” short-term (SQLite hot cache) + long-term archival
* **Transparent audit log** â€” append-only JSONL for all decisions
*  **Resource limits** â€” bounded execution for safe, deterministic behavior

